DAMATURU – NUBAHA Support Organization (NSO) on day gathered at the conference hall of the Nigerian Union of Journalist (NUJ) Secretariat, Damaturu to declare their support for Nuhu Baba Hassan to contest for Member House of Representatives in the forthcoming 2023 election. The groups also donated funds of over 17 million to pay for expression of interest and Nomination form for Nuhu Hassan to contest and represent the good people of Gujba, Gulani, Damaturu and Tarmuwa Federal Constituency in Yobe State. The donors comprise a coalition of 21 youths, farmers and a political group drawn from Gujba, Gulani, Damaturu and Tarmuwa local government areas that makes the Federal Constituency. -Advertisement- In his welcome address, the chairman of NUBAHA Support Organization (NSO), Audu Alhaji Waziri said, they this is part of their support for Nuhu Baba Hassan to come out and contest for the seat of the house of representatives in 2023. “As you can see, Nuhu Baba Hassan is not here but people are trouping in to their support and contributions to see that he succeeded in the forthcoming 2023 election,” said Audu. On his part, the Chairman of the occasion, Mallam Adamu Alaramma stated that Nuhu Baba Hassan deserved to be their representative as he was always identified by the masses around him. He announced the donation of 1 million and 10 bags of beans to the support organization.